12 WHEREAS, across the United States, the week of May 11 through
13 May 17, 2025, is being recognized as "National Police Week"; and
14 WHEREAS, on October 1, 1962, the United States Congress approved
15 a joint resolution authorizing the President of the United States to
16 designate May 15 of each year as "Peace Officers Memorial Day" in
17 honor of law enforcement officers who have been killed, disabled, or
18 otherwise injured in the line of duty and the calendar week during
19 which May 15 occurs as "National Police Week"; and
20 WHEREAS, by proclamation dated May 4, 1963, President John F.
21 Kennedy designated May 15, 1963, and each succeeding May 15 as
22 "Peace Officers Memorial Day" and the week of May 12 through May 18,
23 1963, and each succeeding calendar week during which May 15 occurs
24 as "National Police Week"; and
